org.osmdroid.bonuspack.kml
Class KmlDocument

java.lang.Object
  org.osmdroid.bonuspack.kml.KmlDocument

public class KmlDocument
extends java.lang.Object

Object handling a whole KML document. This is the entry point to read, handle and save KML content.
Features are stored in the kmlRoot attribute, which is a KmlFolder.
Also contains the Shared Styles, referenced in Features using a styleId.
Supports the following KML Geometry: Point, LineString, Polygon and MultiGeometry.
Supports KML Document and Folder hierarchy.
Supports NetworkLink.
Supports GroundOverlay.
Supports LineStyle, PolyStyle and IconStyle - shared and inline.
Supports colorMode: normal, random
Supports ExtendedData inside Features, with support for Data elements and SimpleData elements. In all cases, values are stored as Java String, there is no handling of Schema definition.

Author:
M.Kergall
See Also:
KmlFeature, Style

parseUrl

public boolean parseUrl(java.lang.String url)
Parse a KML document from a url, and build the KML structure in kmlRoot. If the KML file has a "Document" node, kmlRoot will be a Folder "mapping" to this Document. In all other cases, kmlRoot will be a Folder, containing the features of the KML file.

Parameters:
url -
Returns:
true if OK, false if any error.
